You are storing the numbers of each of the coins in the values of the coins, which overwrites those values.  You&#39;re also trying to add the values of the coins before you read the numbers of each of the coins.

You need to store the numbers of each of the coins separately and sum the values after you have read them.

    
    float a, b, c, d;
    a = 0.01;
    b = 0.05;
    c = 0.10;
    d = 0.25;

    int na = 0, nb = 0, nc = 0, nd = 0;



     printf(&quot;How many pennies?&quot;);
     scanf(&quot;%i&quot; , &amp;na);


     printf(&quot;How many nickels?&quot;);
     scanf(&quot;%i&quot;, &amp;nb);


     printf(&quot;How many dimes?&quot;);
     scanf(&quot;%i&quot;, &amp;nc);

     printf(&quot;How many quarters?&quot;);
     scanf(&quot;%i&quot;, &amp;nd);

     printf(&quot;You have $ %.2f\n&quot;, (na * a) + (nb * b) + (nc * c) + (nd * d));

Note, you generally shouldn&#39;t use floating-point values to store monetary values (please see [what every computer scientist should know about floating-point](https://www.itu.dk/~sestoft/bachelor/IEEE754_article.pdf)).

