The Flask-SocketIO server does not know of your application-specific user IDs. What you need to do is create a mapping between the SIDs assigned to each client connection and the user IDs that are represented by each of those clients. You can do this by adding connect and disconnect handlers. Example:

```python
user_to_sid = {}
sid_to_user = {}

@socketio.on(&#39;connect&#39;)
def on_connect(environ):
    user_id = authenticate_user(environ)
    user_to_sid[user_id] = request.sid
    sid_to_user[request.sid] = user_id

@socketio.on(&#39;disconnect&#39;)
def on_disconnect():
    user_id = sid_to_user[request.sid]
    del user_to_sid[user_id]
    del sid_to_user[request.sid]
```

Once you have the mapping, you can easily find the current SID for a given user or viceversa.

