You can create a regex expression from your `names` like so:

    patterns &lt;- paste0(names, collapse = &quot;|&quot;)

and use the `stringr` package to extract these names from `titles` (ignoring case as requested in a comment):

    library(stringr)

    str_match(titles, regex(patterns, ignore_case = TRUE))
    #      [,1]            
    # [1,] &quot;Mike Trout&quot;    
    # [2,] &quot;Mookie Betts&quot;  
    # [3,] &quot;Ronald Acuna&quot;  
    # [4,] &quot;Cody Bellinger&quot;
    # [5,] &quot;Ronald Acuna&quot;  
    # [6,] &quot;Mookie Betts&quot;

This will produce the desired result:

  1. for each element in types
  2. Use value of array (`&amp;1`) as key
  3. Go up 3 levels and copy that as value (`@3`)

```
[
  {
    &quot;operation&quot;: &quot;shift&quot;,
    &quot;spec&quot;: {
      &quot;*&quot;: {
        &quot;types&quot;: {
          &quot;*&quot;: {
            &quot;*&quot;: {
              &quot;@3&quot;: &quot;&amp;1&quot;
